    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, but i've seen people argue that the UN is basically just a tool for whoever holds the most power, like it doesn't really have its own legitimacy if it can't act without the big players. do historians generally view those criticisms as valid critiques of the system, or is it more of a fringe perspective?",
