      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the idealism of \"collective security\" is often undermined by great power politics, many historians argue that the UN still provides essential mechanisms for non-aligned nations. International law, while selectively enforced, establishes crucial norms that smaller states can leverage for protection and advocacy. Therefore, it is not a complete illusion, but rather a system of partial, conditional effectiveness where multilateralism still offers some defense to weaker actors.",
      "source": "target",
